event_description:
As the market evolves, the way VCs evaluate startups has significantly changed. This webinar helps founders understand the real criteria investors are using today. From team and market dynamics to traction and narrative, everything will be analyzed clearly. You will learn what truly builds investor confidence and what causes startups to be rejected early. Join us to gain exclusive insights from an active VC and prepare your startup for successful fundraising. Note: This webinar will be conducted in Vietnamese.

As the venture capital landscape evolves, the criteria investors use to evaluate startups have fundamentally shifted. It is no longer just about a compelling idea; it is about demonstrable proof. This webinar is designed to help founders understand the real, current metrics and qualitative factors that VCs utilize to make funding decisions in 2026.

**❯ What You'll Learn:**

* **Evaluation criteria:** A deep dive into the real, updated criteria investors are using today;
* **Core analysis:** How VCs thoroughly assess your team, market potential, traction, and overall startup narrative;
* **Building confidence:** Key strategies to establish and solidify investor trust during your pitch;
* **Common pitfalls**: Identifying the critical red flags that cause startups to be rejected early in the fundraising process.

**❯ Who Should Attend:**

* Early-stage founders preparing for their upcoming fundraising rounds;
* Entrepreneurs seeking to understand the current venture capital landscape and expectations;
* Anyone interested in the internal evaluation processes of successful early-stage VC firms.

.
**❯❯ This is a live, interactive online event, so be sure to RSVP at [https://fi.co/e/395903/meetup](https://fi.co/e/395903/meetup) to receive the Zoom URL to join us live!**
